headlines.description: — Cam Thomas scored 33 points, and the Brooklyn Nets built a 21-point, first-quarter lead and held on to defeat the Charlotte Hornets 133-121 on Monday night for their first win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Thomas scores 33, Nets use big 1st quarter to beat Hornets 133-121 for 1st win

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic scored nine of his 24 points in the fourth quarter, and the Chicago Bulls rallied past the Indiana Pacers 112-105 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Vucevic helps the Bulls rally past the Pacers for a 112-105 win

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 36 points and Jayson Tatum had 33 as the Boston Celtics won their third straight to open the season, cruising past the Washington Wizards 126-107 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaylen Brown scores 36 points as Celtics race past Wizards 126-107

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray matched his career high with 41 points and the Atlanta Hawks bounced back from a 19-point halftime deficit to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 127-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dejounte Murray ties career high with 41 points, rallies Hawks past Timberwolves 127-113

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant scored 22 points, Deandre Ayton had 10 points and a career-high 23 rebounds and the Portland Trail Blazers won their first game of the season by beating the Toronto Raptors 99-91 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jerami Grant scores 22 as Trail Blazers beat Raptors 99-91 for 1st win of season

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 35 points, 12 rebounds and 12 assists and Derrick Jones Jr. added 22 points as the Dallas Mavericks remained undefeated with a 125-110 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic's 58th career triple-double powers Mavericks past Grizzlies 125-110

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo showed up for his postgame press conference dressed as The Incredible Hulk to celebrate Halloween following Milwaukee's win over Miami.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo, Lillard help Bucks build big lead, hold off Heat in playoff rematch

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — After Stephen Curry let it fly from 31 feet for his seventh made 3-pointer of the night, he crouched at mid-court and punctuated his latest memorable performance by punching his chest once with both fists.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry hits 7 3-pointers, scores 42, as the Warriors roll past the Pelicans 130-102.

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Thunder coach Mark Daigneault got the response he was hoping for.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 32 as Thunder top Pistons 124-112

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 27 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds for his second triple-double of the season, Jamal Murray added 18 points and 14 assists, and the Denver Nuggets continued their strong start to the season with a 110-102 win over the Utah Jazz...
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic posts 107th career triple-double as Nuggets beat Jazz 110-102 for 4th straight win

events.name: Orlando Magic at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell scored 12 of his 28 points in the fourth quarter, LeBron James added nine of his 19 in the final period, and the Los Angeles Lakers rallied for a 106-103 victory over the Orlando Magic on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: D'Angelo Russell comes up big with 12 points in 4th quarter of Lakers' 106-103 win over Orlando
